The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The city and its adjoining areas experienced intermittent power cuts on Monday evening, following a drop in the supply from the state electricity board to the CESC grid. Officials said a 210-MW unit at state-owned Bakreswar thermal power plant collapsed early on Monday. Power department sources said a small fire had broken out in the unit. Repairs are likely to be over by December 15. The state board supplied about 158 MW to the CESC grid on Monday evening.

 A Calcutta High Court division bench on Monday stayed an order passed by Justice S. Sen restraining the Calcutta Municipal Corporation (CMC) from collecting permission fees from advertisement agencies hiring billboards. Justice Sen held that the CMC had no right to collect tax from the agencies. 

 Sadhana Sen, 60, was injured after being knocked down by 

 a taxi at the crossing of CR Avenue and Zakaria Street, 

 under Jorasanko police station, on Sunday. She was admitted 

 to Medical College and Hospital. The driver was arrested 

 and the vehicle impounded. 

 Bishnu Shaw, 18, was injured after being hit by a taxi 

 on Baisnab Seth Street, under Jorabagan police station, 

 on Sunday. He was admitted to Medical College and Hospital. 

 The driver fled with his vehicle. 

 Pappu, 32, a resident of GJ Khan Road in Tiljala, died on Sunday after falling off the staircase of the three-storeyed building where he lived. Police said Pappu was climbing down the stairs carrying a bucket full of water. He was taken to National Medical College and Hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

 A house was gutted and five others were partially damaged in a fire that broke out in Mathur Babu Lane, Tangra, on Monday noon. Fire brigade sources said two tenders were pressed into service. There was no report of injury. 

 Residents of Andul Panchpara, under Howrahs Sankrail police station, have been suffering a monkey menace over the past few days. At least 17 persons have been attacked by a monkey in the past week. Pradip Dutta, additional district forest officer, said a team with sleep-inducing bullets is trying to catch the animal.

 Women passengers organised a sit-in at Sealdah station on Monday, demanding a whole coach be reserved for them. The protesters alleged that they have to suffer daily because only half of a coach is reserved for them and the other half is used by vendors.

 Rupa Saha, 19, committed suicide by hanging herself at her residence in Habra, on the northern fringes of the city, on Sunday night. Police said some local youths used to tease her regularly. 

 Santosh Chowrasia, 30, and Sudip Adhikary, 28, died after the motorcycle they were riding was hit by a truck on BT Road, in Sodepur, on the northern fringes of the city, early on Monday. Police said the duo was heading towards Barrackpore. Santosh was from Delhi and had come to Sudip, a Howrah resident, for business purpose. 

 A fire broke out at a garment factory in Kasba industrial estate on Monday evening. Fire department sources said four tenders were pressed into service. An electrical short-circuit might have caused the fire. 

 TO Rotary Club of Calcutta city of Joy for distributing stationery among students of Holy Child night school




